Context: During a Psychological Crisis/Incident, individuals are expected to report any observed or reported crisis immediately. A psychological crisis may exist when an individual is threatening to do harm or is doing harm to themselves, others, and/or campus property. The phone numbers for reporting such incidents are 416-415-2000 and TTY: 1-877-515-5559, with the email address being ask.george@georgebrown.ca. The college's social media hub can also be visited for further information. It is important to note that the information contained in this website is subject to change without notice and students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
